seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview:
The fourth season of The Block premiered on Monday, 20 June 2011 at 7:00 pm on the Nine Network. Host Scott Cam returned from the previous season, with Shelley Craft joining the series as "Challenge Master".

Unlike previous series, the fourth season was filmed in Melbourne rather than Sydney, with the four houses to be renovated located in the inner-city suburb of Richmond.

The season was ultimately won by Polly Porter and Warwick "Waz" Jones, who were the only couple to sell their property at auction.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview:
The fifth season of The Block premiered on Monday, 16 April 2012 at 7:00 pm on the Nine Network. Both host Scott Cam and "Challenge Master" Shelley Craft returned from the previous season.

Like the previous season, this season was filmed in Melbourne, with the four houses to be renovated located in the inner-city suburb of South Melbourne.

At first, this season wasn't to air in New Zealand, but has now been picked up by TV3. All four previous seasons have aired on Prime.

seasons.name: All Stars
seasons.overview:
The Block All Stars premiered on Monday, 4 February 2013 at 7:00 pm on the Nine Network. Both host Scott Cam and "Challenge Master" Shelley Craft returned from the previous season.

Production for the series relocated from Melbourne—which had hosted the prior two seasons—to its original location of Bondi in Sydney to celebrate the tenth anniversary of the show's first season.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: The four couples are introduced and move into The Block. They randomly draw keys to discover their assigned flat. Everyone is shocked to discover the level of devastation in each apartment. After ripping out horrible old carpets to discover hardwood, one couple finds weak boards...and then termites. An ongoing issue with water leaking from an upstairs apartment creates strife.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Couples work hard to complete their second room for judging. More division between the upstairs and downstairs tenant develops. Poor communication between the tenants results in near electrocution.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: No running water for some and judgment for the next room. More intrigue develops between the neighbors as they continue to spy on each other.

episodes.name: Episode 6

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Emotions run high as all the contestants juggle renovation with their day job responsibilities. They all take a break from the hard work to see Amity launch her singing career at a bar around the corner.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Emotions run high as all the contestants juggle renovation with their day job responsibilities. They all take a break from the hard work to see Amity launch her singing career at a bar around the corner.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Room four winners are revealed. The front garden and attic spaces are still a point of contention as every dollar must be accounted. Amity's dream of becoming a recording artist move closer to reality.

episodes.name: Episode 10

episodes.name: Episode 11

episodes.name: Grand Finale Auction

episodes.name: Reno Rumble (Part 1)
episodes.overview: The original four couples from The Block return as a team to compete against designers from other home improvement shows. The 'Reno'vation Rumble pits the two teams against a one week clock to refurbish identical homes to be given to a local childhood cancer charity.

episodes.name: Reno Rumble (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Despite the need to cooperate to complete the tasks for charity, one team completely unravels while a trip to the pub becomes a point of contention for the other. One team show much better organization than the other. One team fails to deliver the first four rooms on time, even after negotiating an extension.

Another time extension makes it possible for both teams to finish even though not all team members work the final day. The winners are announced. Families are given the keys to the new homes.

episodes.overview: The issue of noise restrictions is a hot topic, and now Dan is upset at Dale about breaking the rules. Scott Cam and Shelley Craft review progress as the couples struggle to complete their bathrooms.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: The Block's judges - Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze and John McGrath - review their decision about the teams' guest rooms and powder rooms, and the couples give their views of their neighbours' efforts.

episodes.name: Room Reveal
episodes.overview: Host Scott Cam calls tools down on the teams as they complete their main bathroom and laundry in time for the judges. There's turmoil as one couple is accused of cheating.

episodes.name: Challenge
episodes.overview: Challenge master Shelley Craft takes the teams to Daylesford in country Victoria, where they will have just five hours to style a room for Belle Magazine and be judged by editor Neale Whitaker.

episodes.name: Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: In their race to complete a bedroom and their hallways, some teams try to cut corners, which puts them in the firing line with site foreman Keith. Host Scott Cam tries to teach Dan how to say no to Dani, with hilarious results.

episodes.name: Scotty's Workshop Challenge
episodes.overview: Host Scott Cam brings in some very tough clients and judges as the teams are set the task of building the world's best cubbyhouse in the workshop challenge.

episodes.name: Scott and Shelley Walk Around The Block
episodes.overview: The teams have finally reached the halfway mark in their renovations and reflect on the last 50 days living at the block. Scott and Shelley stop by to see how the teams are progressing with their hallways and guest bedrooms.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: The judges - Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze and John McGrath - review their decision about the teams' main bathrooms and laundries, and the couples give their views of their neighbours' efforts.

episodes.name: Room Reveal
episodes.overview: The teams are working all-nighters again in their efforts to complete their guest rooms and hallways. Judges award one team the highest scores of the series so far to win the weekly $5000 prize.

episodes.name: Challenge
episodes.overview: The teams are blessed by local priest Father Bob before setting out on a challenge set by Shelley Craft to raise money for his foundation to feed the homeless.

episodes.name: Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: The teams are trying to protect their city views during the renovations of their rooftop terraces, and everyone is hoping for divine intervention as they face the crowds at the charity auction to raise money for Father Bob.

episodes.name: Scotty's Workshop Challenge
episodes.overview: Host Scott Cam presents the couples with the toughest challenge they have faced: The winner will be the team who can complete the most renovation tasks in one 24-hour period.

episodes.name: Scott and Shelley Walk Around The Block
episodes.overview: The teams are juggling budget problems with the needs of getting trades and materials in order to complete this week's rooms. With just a day to go every team is feeling the stress of another very tough week on the tools.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: The Block's judges - Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze and John McGrath - review their decision about the teams' main bathrooms and laundry areas.

episodes.name: Room Reveal
episodes.overview: With just four hours to go until room reveal, all four teams are rushing to complete their rooftop terraces in time for the judges. As budgets are getting tighter, everyone is desperate to win the $5000 weekly room prize.

episodes.name: Shelley Craft's Challenge
episodes.overview: Challenge master Shelley Craft wakes the couples at 4am for this challenge, which kicks off at Melbourne's famous flower markets, where she unveils a very rare botanical money tree.

episodes.name: Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: One team has a very difficult decision to make as they can double their winnings by reaching into their neighbours' pockets. The brothers try to keep their room swap a secret from the others.

episodes.name: Scotty's Workshop Challenge
episodes.overview: Scott Cam welcomes game-show host Ed Phillips to the workshop to kick off a big money guessing competition and a magical mystery tour around Melbourne.

episodes.name: Scott and Shelley Walk Around The Block
episodes.overview: A team member is rushed to hospital with an illness, which leaves his partner at home to fend for herself in trying to complete the living room. Her neighbours then have to decide if they can leave their renovations to come to her rescue.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: The judges - Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze, and John McGrath - review their decision about the teams' renovations of their roof terraces, and the couples give their views of their neighbours' efforts.

episodes.name: Room Reveal
episodes.overview: After three days in hospital, Dale finally returns to the block, just in time to help Sophie finish their living room in time for judgement day.

episodes.name: Shelley Craft's Challenge
episodes.overview: All four teams make a start on their kitchens. Challenge master Shelley Craft welcomes some familiar faces as newly engaged couple Polly and Waz and Josh and Jenna return to the block to set the new teams a wedding challenge.

episodes.name: Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: With kitchens and an extra room to complete, all four teams are under the pump to deliver this week. Lara takes charge of the renovations in her house when Brad leaves the block and impresses site foreman Keith with her new renovation.

episodes.name: Scotty's Workshop Challenge
episodes.overview: Scott Cam sets the teams a workshop challenge to create a dining table from scratch and then turns the tables when they discover their creations will be going on public display in Melbourne's busiest street.

episodes.name: Scott and Shelley Walk Around The Block
episodes.overview: The public get to vote for the winner of yesterday's massive challenge and everybody hopes for a win as their budgets are now extremely tight. And Brad and Lara come up with a novel idea for the splashback in their kitchen island.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: The Block's judges, Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze and John McGrath review their decision about the teams renovations of their living rooms and the couples give their views of their neighbours efforts.

episodes.name: Room Reveal
episodes.overview: With a double-room week and a prize of $10,000 up for grabs, the four teams are in a race to complete their kitchens and their room savers in time for judging.

episodes.name: Shelley Craft's Challenge
episodes.overview: Lara hits rock bottom when she and Brad run out of money, but Shelley comes to the rescue with a challenge to build a barbecue and potentially save their budgets. The Melbourne Storm are guest judges.

episodes.name: Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: Brad and Lara believe foreman Keith has it in for them when he asks for changes to their outdoor plans. Next-door neighbours Dan and Dani are desperately trying to achieve a garden design with very little budget remaining.

episodes.name: Scotty's Workshop Challenge
episodes.overview: Scott Cam and Shelley Craft take the contestants out for a sports-day challenge. Each couple will represent their house colours as they battle to win much-needed cash for their garden renovations.

episodes.name: Scott and Shelley Walk Around The Block
episodes.overview: The teams are back at the block and hard at work on their exteriors. Once the fences go up between the houses, one team finds themselves completely blocked off. Mike and Andrew finally meet the descendants of the original owners of their home.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Judges Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze, and John McGrath review their decision about the teams' renovations of their kitchens and 'room savers' and the couples give their views of their neighbours' efforts.

episodes.name: Room Reveal
episodes.overview: After 10 weeks of renovating, the teams are now racing to complete their most challenging room delivery - their gardens and front facades of their homes. The winning team will take home $5000 in gold bullion.

episodes.name: Challenge Week Commences
episodes.overview: The couples are packing up to move out of the block, but host Scott Cam surprises them with a massive, week-long renovation challenge that could determine the winner of the competition.

episodes.name: Challenge Week Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: Day two of the final challenge, and the scale of the project ahead of them is proving daunting for everyone. Site foreman Keith predicts that time management will prove the downfall of one team.

episodes.name: Scott and Shelley Walk Around The Challenge House
episodes.overview: After three long days of renovating, the teams are battling with each other to deliver the best results. Everyone is relying on the skills learned over the past 10 weeks to get them through.

episodes.name: Challenge House Room Reveal
episodes.overview: In the race to the finish line, all four teams are desperate to get an edge over the competition and complete the challenge in time for the special guest judges.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: In this final episode of Unlocked the teams reflect on their renovations and prepare for their open for inspections and the all-important auction day.

episodes.name: The Block Auction Grand Finale
episodes.overview: All four houses go up for public auction. Each team will keep the profit they make over reserve and the team with the highest margin will also win the grand prize of $100,000.

5.name: Season 5
5.overview:
The fifth season of The Block premiered on Monday, 16 April 2012 at 7:00 pm on the Nine Network. Both host Scott Cam and "Challenge Master" Shelley Craft returned from the previous season.

Like the previous season, this season was filmed in Melbourne, with the four houses to be renovated located in the inner-city suburb of South Melbourne.

At first, this season wasn't to air in New Zealand, but has now been picked up by TV3. All four previous seasons have aired on Prime.

episodes.name: Move Into The Block
episodes.overview: Four all star couples are given with the toughest renovation challenge they have ever faced. In just six weeks they will have to completely make over four heritage listed homes in one of the suburbs best streets.

episodes.name: Charity Makeover Challenge
episodes.overview: The enormity of the challenge ahead starts to sink in as they encounter the strict heritage rules. In the midst of this Scott Cam sends them on a challenge to makeover rooms at the Sydney Children's Hospital.

episodes.name: The Safe Opens
episodes.overview: The teams race to complete their rooms in time for the judges. The winning team will donate $5000 to a charity of their choice and also win a code that will allow them to open one of their neighbours safes at The Block.

episodes.name: Bedroom 1 Reveal
episodes.overview: In a race against the clock, the teams discover that completing heritage listed rooms is far harder than they ever imagined.

episodes.name: Bedroom 2 Renovations Begins
episodes.overview: The competition heats up as the All Stars inspect each other's completed first rooms. Beginning work on their second rooms, the teams get busy designing the rest of their house while trying to deal with the heritage restrictions.

episodes.name: Bedroom 2 Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: Bedroom two is well underway and one of our couples is planning ahead, meeting with a real estate agent and inspecting other Bondi properties.

episodes.name: Restoration Nation Challenge
episodes.overview: One team is hit with some devastating family news, while another comes up with a potential game changing plan for the back of their house. Shelley has a creative repurposing challenge for the teams where the prize is valued at over $20,000.

episodes.name: Scott and Shelley Walk Around The Block
episodes.overview: Scott gets one team closer to opening another Suzuki safe. All the teams race to finish their second bedrooms but for one team member, the pressure of being an All Star weighs heavily and becomes all too much.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Go behind the scenes with judges Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze and newcomer Darren Palmer as they review their judging of the very first All Stars room reveals.

episodes.name: Bedroom 2 Reveal
episodes.overview: With only a day before delivery of their second bedrooms, the teams struggle to finish ahead of judging. There's another $5,000 up for grabs but the judges are so impressed with the standard they have trouble choosing a winner.

episodes.name: Bathroom Renovations Begin
episodes.overview: Bathrooms are next on the All Stars renovation list and all the teams are trying to impress. But some couples face delays as foreman Keith keeps a close eye on construction.

episodes.name: The Block Olympian Challenge
episodes.overview: Bathroom week, aka Hell Week, continues. One team is already behind due to a problem with their flooring and all the teams face some time consuming heritage work ahead of them.

episodes.name: The Belle Bathroom Challenge
episodes.overview: Challenge Queen Shelley Craft surprises everyone with a bathroom display challenge and the chance to have their bathroom feature in Belle Magazine.

episodes.name: Hell Week Continues
episodes.overview: With only a few days left to finish their bathrooms, the pressure is on. One teams is faced with the huge task of fixing floor levels, while another finds quirky bathroom accessories.

episodes.name: Dani Takes Charge
episodes.overview: One all-star is struck down with a stomach bug, leaving his teammate in charge of the bathroom build herself. Keith's on the rampage about one team's extra housemate, a four-legged friend.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Go behind the scenes with judges Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze and newcomer Darren Palmer as they review their judging of the second room of The Block.

episodes.name: Bathroom Reveal
episodes.overview: Careful planning and hard work pay off with the all-stars delivering the best bathrooms this series has ever seen. The judges are surprised by the results, and tensions are high as the scores go down to the wire.

episodes.name: Triple Room Week Begins
episodes.overview: The teams forge ahead with unique plans for the formal lounge, hallway and linen cupboard, aka Ben Hur week. Budgets are tight and all the teams discover they're in desperate need of a win to finish the build out back.

episodes.name: Triple Room Week Continues
episodes.overview: A week this big deserves big prize money and the teams find out just how much they'll win for their formal lounge, hallway and linen cupboards come room reveal.

episodes.name: Go-Karting Challenge
episodes.overview: Scotty presents the teams with two challenges that bring out the artist and the car enthusiast in the all-stars. It's a race to finish three rooms for judging and for one couple, second thoughts on paint colour prove difficult.

episodes.name: The 2nd Safe Opens
episodes.overview: In the race to save time, the two teams try their hand at spray painting, and for one team, it doesn't end well. Delays to the ongoing build out the back force two teams to call an urgent meeting and confront foreman Keith.

episodes.name: Brad and Lara Return
episodes.overview: As the teams race to finish their formal lounge, hallways and linen cupboards, lack of sleep starts to affect everyone. For some, tempers boil over, for others, it becomes all too much. The winner of the art car challenge is announced.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Go behind the scenes with judges Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze and newcomer Darren Palmer as they review their judging of the Bathroom room reveals.

episodes.name: Triple Room Reveal
episodes.overview: Living room, hallway and utility room week has made some of the teams tired and emotional. As all their hard work comes together, the end results are four very different looks.

episodes.name: Someone Leaves The Block
episodes.overview: The All Stars dust themselves off after the judges comments and the claws come out as they inspect each others rooms. Two teams join forces to win more money, but these petty politics are overshadowed by a tragic incident.

episodes.name: Kitchen Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: Mark's health scare takes its toll on all the contestants and Duncan gets a helping hand. Phil and Amity's unique addition in the back of their house is shaping up well and one team has problems with the heritage chimney.

episodes.name: New Arrival on The Block
episodes.overview: Shelley has a challenge that will bring out the inner stylist in the All Stars. The teams must style a multi million dollar apartment then do their best as novice real estate agents as they show the properties to buyers.

episodes.name: Dan Unchained
episodes.overview: With three days before the All Stars deliver their kitchens and laundries, some teams get personal with each others' kitchen finishes. Mark and his new partner are a day and a half behind and risk not finishing their rooms.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Catch up on a tumultuous week and learn what the judges really think about the couples' completed rooms.

episodes.name: Kitchen Reveal
episodes.overview: The heat is on as kitchens are installed, and all the teams have something unique that they hope will make theirs the winning room. The scores come down to nearly full marks for two couples, and true colours are revealed.

episodes.name: War on The Block
episodes.overview: The finished kitchens are open for inspection, and the claws come out when the couples disagree with the judges.

episodes.name: Dan Strips for Charity
episodes.overview: The budgets are stretched in the final stages of the All Star renovations and there's a big win for one team when they open a safe.

episodes.name: Bondi Sculpture Challenge
episodes.overview: Living room week is in full swing. The All Stars spend the night away and try their hands as artists in Shelley's sculpture challenge, the final challenge of the series.

episodes.name: Phil's Revenge
episodes.overview: The living rooms and gardens are almost complete. For one team, a wrong measurement spells disaster in the garden and paint spraying in the living room means time lost instead of time saved.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: The judges hand down their final verdict on the completed kitchens as the couples race to finish their houses.

episodes.name: Living Room Reveal
episodes.overview: Its a busy time for the All Stars as they put on smiles and race to finish their living rooms. The winners of living room week receive $5000, a prize much needed by all the teams in order to finish their outdoor areas.

episodes.name: Exterior Renovations Continue
episodes.overview: Its the final two days as the teams race to finish both the front and back gardens. As the facades come together Scotty presents our couples with name plaques for each house and for two competitors, the mood is particularly festive.

episodes.name: Exterior Reveal
episodes.overview: The All Stars face a huge clean up as they make the finishing touches to their gardens. The judges are joined by real estate expert John McGrath as they give their final scores and for two couples, the results are closer than ever before.

episodes.name: The Block: All Stars Auction Grand Finale
episodes.overview: All four houses go up for public auction. Each team will keep the profit they make over reserve and the team with the highest margin will also win the grand prize of $100,000.

6.name: All Stars
6.overview:
The Block All Stars premiered on Monday, 4 February 2013 at 7:00 pm on the Nine Network. Both host Scott Cam and "Challenge Master" Shelley Craft returned from the previous season.

Production for the series relocated from Melbourne—which had hosted the prior two seasons—to its original location of Bondi in Sydney to celebrate the tenth anniversary of the show's first season.

episodes.name: Meeting the Teams
episodes.overview: This series it's state versus state and five new teams check into The Biz Hotel where they meet host Scott Cam who puts them straight to work with a massive challenge. They're given $10,000 and 48 hours to renovate a bedroom and bathroom.

episodes.name: First Challenge
episodes.overview: Half way through their first challenge and the contestants are faced with all kinds of setbacks. For one team, a burst water pipe causes headaches, and for another, a visit to the emergency department leaves one team one man down.

episodes.name: Hotel Room Reveal
episodes.overview: The 48 hour challenge is over. Neale Whitaker, Shaynna Blaze and Darren Palmer judge the challenge rooms. And the teams move into the new apartments they will call home for the next 9 weeks.

episodes.name: Bedroom Renovations continue
episodes.overview: Five bedrooms and five bathrooms on five levels all being renovated in a week means leaks, delays and stress for the teams. Keith is on the prowl, making sure all the teams build their rooms correctly.

episodes.name: Shelley's Bedlam Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants meet Shelley who puts their creative skills to the test with a challenge. There's $5000 up for grabs for the winner and Scotty has a special surprise that will help them all win money over the coming weeks.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Catch up on all the drama of the week and learn the design secrets of each couple as they guide you through their completed rooms. Hosted by Shelley Craft.

episodes.name: Bedroom/ensuite Room Reveal
episodes.overview: The teams complete their first bedroom and ensuite. One couple shock the judges, delivering the most controversial room The Block has ever seen. The winners are announced and take home a massive $10,000 in cash from NAB.

episodes.name: Double ensuite week begins
episodes.overview: The teams inspect each other's completed rooms and not everyone agrees with the judges. With two bathrooms up for judging at the end of the week, the competition heats up when two teams decide to install a steam room in one of their ensuites.

episodes.name: Steam Room Scandal
episodes.overview: Double bathroom week gets ultra competitive with everyone, including the team's tradies, trying to outdo each other. Two teams battle it out over their secret steam rooms while the other teams simply try to stop the water leaks.

episodes.name: Tough Mudders Challenge
episodes.overview: There's a welcome distraction from Block politics when the teams meet Scotty for their next challenge where there's a $5000 prize.

episodes.name: Paint Roller Wars
episodes.overview: Its double bathroom week and some of the teams get started on the enormous task of painting the building's exterior. A good deed from one contestant backfires leading to a war between two teams.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked - Bedroom/Ensuite Room
episodes.overview: Catch up on all the drama of the week and learn the design secrets of each couple as they guide you through their completed rooms. Hosted by Shelley Craft.

episodes.name: His and Hers Ensuites Room Reveal
episodes.overview: Double bathroom week comes to a close with the inspiring his and hers ensuites being delivered. Judges Neale, Shaynna and Darren are wowed by all 10 bathrooms and have trouble deciding a winner.

episodes.name: Teams Team Up
episodes.overview: Critical opinions are out in the open when the teams inspect each others his and hers ensuites. Alliances are formed when secrets are heard from around The Block And there's excitement for one couple with some special visitors arriving.

episodes.name: Bec's Birthday Surprise
episodes.overview: Some contestants take time out to celebrate a very special birthday. After foreman Keith disapproves of one teams efforts at insulating their bedroom they throw in the towel and walk off The Block.

episodes.name: All Stars Tour The Block
episodes.overview: Shelley has a creative challenge for the teams where a $3000 prize is up for grabs. The Block gets some special visitors that has all the teams talking.

episodes.name: Scott & Shelley walk around The Block
episodes.overview: Nearing the end of master bedroom and dressing room week, one team have come up with a design that will impress the judges and future buyers.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Catch up on all the drama of the week and learn the design secrets of each couple as they guide you through their completed rooms. Hosted by Shelley Craft.

episodes.name: Master Bedroom Room Reveal
episodes.overview: The judges are wowed by the master bedrooms and dressing rooms and all the teams score well, but one team is left wondering what they need to do to win. Scotty has a special announcement that takes everyone by surprise.

episodes.name: New week, new bathroom to reno
episodes.overview: All the teams return to The Block after spending time with their families. Work begins on the last bedroom and fourth bathroom of their luxury apartments but for one team, a family tragedy sees them take some time away from The Block.

episodes.name: Bedhead Bedlam Begins
episodes.overview: It's day 40 and the teams rally together to help George and Bec progress in their room. The bed heads from Shelley's very first challenge arrive, and foreman Keith finds out that not everyone is playing by the rules.

episodes.name: The Return of #3
episodes.overview: George and Bec arrive back on The Block. Their absence has widened the gap between the upper and lower floors. As the teams get busy reworking their challenge, trouble brews when everyone has a different interpretation of the rules.

episodes.name: Baby Brain Challenge and Madi vs Matt
episodes.overview: Shelley has another challenge for the Blockheads and this time they are creating beautiful baby nurseries for some very pregnant mothers. Madi does some snooping and dobs in another team for not following the bed head rules.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Shelley Craft shows all the best unseen moments of the week that was on The Block. Judges Neale, Shaynna and Darren give an insight into their scoring and which teams to watch.

episodes.name: Guest Bedroom and Ensuite Room Reveal
episodes.overview: In the race to finish the final bedroom and ensuite, one contestant calls a body corporate meeting. The judges inspect the rooms and the winning couple is surprised when they win by just half a point, taking home $10,000.

episodes.name: Kitchen week starts
episodes.overview: The final bedrooms and bathrooms are open for inspection, and not all the teams are happy. But there's no time for grudges with major demolition work starting to make way for new kitchens.

episodes.name: Shellys Weekly Challenge
episodes.overview: The teams begin week five with a challenge at the People's Market in Collingwood. Alliances hold strong when one team is accused of cheating. Back at the Block renovations continue, some pour their concrete floor while others prepare for water leaks.

episodes.name: Financial worries
episodes.overview: As the challenge continues so does the candle scandal. And when the winners are announced and numbers are crunched, one team is almost broke while another has almost $30,000 in winnings.

episodes.name: Kitchen Week Controversy + Another birthday on the Block
episodes.overview: The competition in kitchen week is fierce and one team speaks in code so they don't give away their plans. But even in the busiest week of competition, the teams enjoy some time out for a birthday celebration.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Shelley Craft shows all the best unseen moments of the week that was on The Block. Judges Neale, Shaynna and Darren give an insight into their scoring and which teams to watch.

episodes.name: Kitchen Room Reveal
episodes.overview: Emotions run high as the teams battle to finish their kitchens and one couple has goods stolen from their apartment. The hard work pays off as the winners score a perfect 10 from one judge and take home a much needed $10,000.

episodes.name: Living and Dining Room Demolition Begins
episodes.overview: The kitchens are open for inspection and the teams have their opinion about each other's rooms. As they move onto their living and dining rooms, Keith is kept very busy supervising demolition on all five levels.

episodes.name: The Halfway Mark
episodes.overview: Officially half way through the competition and contestants are low on funds and exhausted. The teams meet Scotty and Shelley for a challenge like no other. There's big prize money up for grabs plus a big surprise from Scotty.

episodes.name: Living room week continues
episodes.overview: With flooring being laid and furniture arriving, the living rooms are starting to take shape but there's still plenty of renovation to get done. Scotty arrives on site with unexpected gifts for everyone.

episodes.name: Day at the races
episodes.overview: Relationships are tested during the halfway week on The Block. The living and dining rooms are well under way and the teams get the chance to earn some extra cash in a race that stops The Block.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: All the best unseen footage from master bedroom and dressing room week. The judges give their opinions on the best and the worst features from all the master suites.

episodes.name: Room Reveal: Living and Dining Rooms
episodes.overview: The teams prepare to deliver their all-important Living and Dining Rooms and judge Neale Whitaker calls one room perfect. But as the teams anxiously wait to find out who the winners are, Scotty announces a very unexpected twist.

episodes.name: Living and Dining Room Reveal continues
episodes.overview: For the first time in Block history, the contestants get to judge each others rooms, the Living Room. And after deals are made... and broken, the final scores produce a surprising winner. Work begins on the Foyer and Laundries.

episodes.name: Challenge Day - Billy Cart Bandits
episodes.overview: Foyer and Laundry week continues and all the teams are under pressure to deliver the wow factor. Special guests, Mike and Andrew from The Block 2012 arrive and bring with them a creative challenge that gets the teams racing.

episodes.name: The Blockinator Break Out
episodes.overview: Keith The Blockinator breaks loose on The Block and no team is safe. One team's relationship is under pressure while another team becomes the brunt of a prank that sees them camping out and losing sleep.

episodes.name: Reality
episodes.overview: All the teams finally find their secret weapons for this weeks Foyers and Laundries due to be delivered by Sunday. Kim goes solo as Matt is out with a bad back and Madi gets pranked ... again.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: The judges reflect on last weeks Living and Dining rooms. And we take a peak at some inside stories as the teams are headed to deliver their Foyer and Laundries.

episodes.name: Room Reveal - Foyer and Laundry
episodes.overview: As the blockheads race to finish their foyers and laundries, some teams are confident of a win while others are confident of a loss but as Scotty reveals the judge's scores there are surprises in store for everyone.

episodes.name: The Last Room of the Apartment: The Terrace Begins
episodes.overview: The completed foyers and laundries are open for inspection and the teams don't hold back their opinions on each others completed rooms. The teams start work on the last room of their apartments, the terraces.

episodes.name: The Terrace
episodes.overview: The Myer Window Challenge winner is announced. The couples then continue to work on their terraces and fix-up rooms.

episodes.name: Reality Hump Day
episodes.overview: While some contestants get creative with what money they have left in their tight budgets, others have a lot more to spend. All the teams are trying their best to impress, choosing vertical gardens and designer furniture.

episodes.name: The Block Sky High
episodes.overview: Indecision strikes one team after they work late into the night with little sleep on their terraces and re-do rooms. After eight weeks of renovating and a holiday to Lizard Island on offer for the winner, there's tension on every level.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked - Foyer and Laundry
episodes.overview: The judges reflect on last week's judging of the foyers and laundries. Plus we take a peak at some inside stories as the teams deliver their terrace and re-do Rooms.

episodes.name: Terrace and Re-Do Room Reveal
episodes.overview: After a huge rush and a sleepless night for most, the terraces are ready for the judges verdict. This week's prize is a surprise to the Blockheads, and the winners are the envy of the four remaining teams.

episodes.name: Team Work Together
episodes.overview: The completed terraces are open for inspection and some of the contestants question how the winning team came up with the cash. The teams must pull together for the first time to begin work on the communal roof top and entrance foyer.

episodes.name: Rooftop and Entrance Foyer
episodes.overview: The Blockheads struggle to work as a team as they get busy with the communal areas of the building. There's confusion, finger pointing and tantrums but the clock is ticking and the teams need to deliver by the end of the week.

episodes.name: Rooftop Terrace and Entrance Foyer
episodes.overview: Scotty calls in to check the progress of the entrance foyer and rooftop terrace. Madi plays a payback prank and tempers fray as the competition takes its toll. Plus there's a designing challenge worth $5000 up for grabs.

episodes.name: Matt, the Foreman
episodes.overview: Frustrated by the progress of work from the other teams, one Blockhead decides to take control as foreman, but there are problems. The winners of the challenge claim their prize - breakfast and advice with judge Neale Whitaker.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked - Terrace and Re-Do Room
episodes.overview: The judges reflect on the judging of the terrace. Plus we take a peak at some inside stories and unseen footage from the previous week.

episodes.name: The Challenge Level Begins
episodes.overview: The Blockheads continue to work on the two communal areas, the entry foyer and rooftop. All their hard work is rewarded when their families arrive to spend some quality time together. But Scotty's got another surprise that no one expects.

episodes.name: Back to Renovating
episodes.overview: Scotty's unexpected surprise brings mixed emotions and while some contestants rise to the challenge and get on with the job, others aren't impressed with what lies ahead.

episodes.name: Fighting with the Foreman
episodes.overview: After weeks of renovating, tempers are frayed and there's a showdown between Keith and one of our couples. Trixie and Johnno's progress is slow, holding up the job in Matt and Kim's room.

episodes.name: Real Estate Challenge
episodes.overview: When the teams are are busier than ever, Scotty announces one final challenge. The teams have to create a video that markets their own apartment for sale. There's $5000 up for grabs to finish their extra rooms.

episodes.name: Keith's Soft Side
episodes.overview: The dust settles after the showdown between Keith and Bec and George, and Bec sees Keith's softer side. Kim goes on a research mission for a quirky new business idea.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked - Exterior, Foyer & Rooftop
episodes.overview: Catch up on all the drama of the week and learn the design secrets of each couple as they guide you through their completed rooms. Hosted by Shelley Craft.

episodes.name: Game Changing Prizes
episodes.overview: After a huge week of team work the first week of ground floor renovating is complete and the judges' scores are in. First place is to be rewarded $20,000 off reserve.

episodes.name: The Final Week Begins
episodes.overview: The losers from the judging speak their mind when the completed rooms are open for inspection. Work begins on the second spaces on the ground floor. Some have a chance to showcase their landscaping talents.

episodes.name: Keith the Problem Solver Foreman
episodes.overview: It's the final week on The Block and the tradesmen on-site do their best to work together. Foreman Keith solves a multitude of logistical problems which is lucky for the contestants.

episodes.name: Johnno Goes Sky High
episodes.overview: It's the final 24 hours on The Block and Scotty visits for his customary walk through to check on progress.

episodes.name: The Final Scores Are In
episodes.overview: The final scores are in and one couple gets a perfect 30 out of 30 from the judges. The results also reveal that one team will have a whopping $30,000 taken off their reserve price on auction day.

episodes.name: The Block Unlocked
episodes.overview: Catch up on all the drama of the week and learn the design secrets of each couple as they guide you through their completed rooms. Hosted by Shelley Craft.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: All five apartments go under the hammer. The reserve prices are announced and after five intense auctions, the 2013 winner is announced.

episodes.name: Scott and Shelley Walk Around the Block
Guest Bathroom, Laundry, Drying Terrace Room Reveal
The Block Unlocked 3 (Guest Bathroom, Laundry, Drying Terrace)
Living and Dining On A Budget
The Block Unlocked (Living and Dining Rooms)
Jimmy Possum Challenge
episodes.overview: It's half way through bedroom week and Jess flies to Sydney to shop with Neale Whitaker, who has some helpful design and styling advice. Then its challenge time and the teams drive to Bendigo where they meet Scotty at furniture manufacturers Jimmy Possum.

episodes.name: The Battle Of The Seagrass Wallpaper
episodes.overview: The battle of the seagrass wallpaper continues. The teams are stopping at nothing to impress the judges this week. Scotty and Shelley arrive on site to check on progress and Josh is faced with a major set back when Keith tells him to start his flooring again.

episodes.name: The Block Open House 3
episodes.overview: Tonight Block All Stars winners Phil and Amity help a Sydney family who are struggling to sell their home. Keith and Dan get together in the shed and make some stunning side tables.

episodes.name: Bedrooms Revealed
episodes.overview: The battle of the seagrass wallpaper heats up when the second bedrooms are revealed and the judges are divided on one room. Neale loves it, but Shaynna isn't so keen and things heat up at Scotty's HQ when Dea and Darren wield the power of the chalk.

episodes.name: Buyers Jury
episodes.overview: The teams start work on their laundries, powder rooms, and cellars. Then the teams head to meet Scotty and Shelley at HQ to hear some all-important feedback from the buyer's jury.

episodes.name: Make A Wish Challenge
episodes.overview: Midway through a mammoth three room week, there's plenty of renovating on The Block, and challenge day comes at a very busy time. The contestants meet Shelley for a special Make A Wish Challenge, and all involved help put a smile on the faces of some unwell children.

episodes.name: Three Room Reality
episodes.overview: Tempers fray as one contestant wants to quit. There's tiling gone wrong, laundry chute issues and floor levels that aren't right. Ayden and Jess's receive a welcome distraction when their children arrive for a visit.

episodes.name: The Block Open House 4: Bedroom 2 Review
episodes.overview: Shelley will fill you in with all the best behind the scenes from the past week of renovating on The Block. Glasshouse winners Simon and Shannon help out a Sydney family in the latest "Doing Your Block". Design Doctor Darren Palmer helps a couple design a nursery

episodes.name: Powder Room, Laundry and Cellar Reveal
episodes.overview: It's the end of a massive week of renovating when the four teams complete their powder rooms, laundries and cellars. The judges are impressed with all the rooms and when it comes to the scores, there's just half a point difference for three of the teams.

episodes.name: Buyers Jury
episodes.overview: When the team's inspect each others rooms, there is controversy over the cost of Darren and Dea's cellar full of wine. The buyers jury also inspects the completed rooms and when it comes to choosing a winner, they don't agree with judges Neale, Shaynna and Darren.

episodes.name: Model Tenants Challenge
episodes.overview: Midway through living and dining room week, Darren and Deanne are frustrated by the demands of the building inspector when they're told their ceiling is too low. The teams meet Scotty for a challenge where they'll need to bring their very best designer foot forward.

episodes.name: Living and Dining Rooms Take Shape
episodes.overview: As the week continues, Anastasia is loosing confidence, Jess and Ayden are fighting and getting furniture into the apartments is proving difficult. Charlotte spends her birthday painting late into the night, taking extra care with the paint to try to impress the judges.

episodes.name: The Block Open House 5: Living & Dining Review
episodes.overview: Shaynna Blaze gives us great advice about how to get the Hollywood regency look at your place. Glasshouse contestants Michael and Carlene are back for Doing Your Block and Scotty rescues another Knucklehead.

episodes.name: Living and Dining Rooms Revealed
episodes.overview: Four exhausted teams deliver their living and dining rooms and in Scotty's HQ, the feedback from the judges is brutal. One team doesn't complete their dining area and another is devastated by the comments they receive.

episodes.name: Shaynna Mentors Dea
episodes.overview: The mess in Dea and Darren's dining room is addressed when Shaynna arrives for a mentoring session. Tim and Anastasia plan a loo with a view in their ensuite. The buyers' advocates score the completed rooms and this week they don't agree with the judges.

episodes.name: Face Value Challenge
episodes.overview: It's challenge day and the teams head to Coburg where they meet Scotty for a landscaping challenge. They'll have eight hours to transform the front gardens of two properties and the winning team will take home $6,000 cash.

episodes.name: Ensuite Week Continues
episodes.overview: Our buyers' advocates arrive in Coburg to decide on a winner of the landscaping challenge. Then the teams head back to the Block and get working on their ensuites. Budgets are on everyone's mind as the invoices roll in and the teams struggle to pay their tradesmen.

episodes.name: The Block Open House
episodes.overview: Block All Stars Matt and Kim help a family sell their home for top dollar, past contestant and professional painter Shannon gives his best painting tips. Design Doctor Darren Palmer works his magic in an incredible bathroom makeover.

episodes.name: Ensuites Revealed
episodes.overview: Four spectacular ensuite bathrooms are revealed. Ayden and Jess struggle to complete their room and the exhausted four teams head to Scotty's HQ to find out who will win this week's much wanted $10,000 cash prize.

episodes.name: Master Bedrooms Begin
episodes.overview: Another week of renovating begins with the master bedrooms. The contestants inspect each others completed ensuites and one team plays to win, giving every other team zero out of ten in The Block jury vote. Keith and Darren aren't seeing eye to eye this week.

episodes.name: Style to Sell Challenge
episodes.overview: Trouble brews for Dea and Darren when the other teams call for an investigation into the cost of the 440 bottles of wine for their cellar. It's challenge day once again and the teams have the chance to win $5000 cash in a real estate styling challenge.

episodes.name: The Wine Audit
episodes.overview: Construction is in full swing, with balconies being installed at each apartment. Scotty and Shelley arrive to check on progress of everyone's master suite. Ayden and Tim do their own investigation on Dea and Darren's cellar full of wine and ask Shelley for a wine audit.

episodes.name: The Block Open House 7: Ensuites Review
Master Bedroom Reveal
episodes.overview: Four very different master bedrooms and dressing rooms are revealed. One team scores a perfect thirty out of thirty but Scotty has a shocking surprise that changes the game. Dea and Darren's wine audit comes to a head when Scotty plays judge and jury.

episodes.name: The Block Triple Threat Special
episodes.overview: Tonight Scott Cam takes you behind the scenes of The Block. You'll see auditions from our chosen contestants as well as entries from some of the thousands of people who want-to-be Blockheads.

episodes.name: Kitchen Week Begins
episodes.overview: The Block's exterior takes shape when rendering begins. The jury votes are rigged as one team is favoured and awarded the $5000 cash. For Tim and Anastasia, kitchen week gets off to a rocky start and Dea and Darren argue with Keith about their depleting budget.

episodes.name: Kitchen Week Continues
episodes.overview: Tonight four very different kitchens are well underway but progress stops when Tim and Anastasia's space isn't ready. Anastasia can't handle the pressure. The staircases begin to take shape.

episodes.name: Challenge Day
episodes.overview: The couples are put into two teams on challenge day and compete against each other as they transform two corporate suites at the MCG. At The Block there's problems for Tim and Anastasia. They're not happy with their kitchen and the installation isn't going to plan.

episodes.name: Kitchens Revealed
episodes.overview: The contestants complete four incredible and very different kitchens, but the judges aren't wowed by the efforts of the Blockheads. Dea and Darren are happy with their kitchen and are surprised and disappointed by feedback. One team takes home $10000.

episodes.name: Study And Stairs
episodes.overview: Another week of renovating begins and the contestants are tired and scared of the enormous job. One team isn't organised and Keith and Dan decide to help out. The buyers advocates judge the completed kitchen and the teams also inspect each others kitchens.

episodes.name: Triple Threat Radio
episodes.overview: Scotty tries his hand at live talk back radio with the contestants. Tim cooks a lamb on a spit as a treat for everyone on site.

episodes.name: Kitchen Capers Challenge
episodes.overview: Midway through a difficult week, the contestants meet chef Matt Moran for a chance to win $5000. Its a great opportunity for the teams to showcase their beautiful new kitchens. Darren finds out that two of the teams have been given extra cash for their staircases.

episodes.name: Staircase Judging
episodes.overview: Tonight marks the end of a huge week for The Block contestants when Scotty calls tools down on staircase and study week. In a Block first, one team receives the lowest scores ever given by the judges, who aren't impressed by anyone's efforts this week.

episodes.name: Terrace Week Begins
episodes.overview: The final week of renovating begins as the teams gear up once again, this time for their outdoor terraces. Dea and Darren get to work finishing rooms in their apartment. Work on the front gardens begins & Tim and Anastasia are struggling with their budget.

episodes.name: Terraces Take Shape
episodes.overview: Foreboy Dan offers a helping hand to Tim and Anastasia. The common areas of The Block take shape and Jess chooses a sculpture for the space. One contestant starts a rumour about Tim and Anastasia's mounting bills to tradesmen.

episodes.name: The Budget Blowout
episodes.overview: If it can go wrong, it will go wrong for one couple on The Block, with budget woes, fighting, the rumour mill in overdrive and confrontation. Scotty is on duty to check on progress and steps in to get to the bottom of Tim and Anastasia's budget issues.

episodes.name: Terraces Revealed
episodes.overview: It's the end of the final week of renovating on The Block and the terraces are handed over for judging. One team triumphs with a perfect thirty out of thirty but sadly one team doesn't finish their terrace.

episodes.name: The Final Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants have seventy two hours to complete their apartments and Scotty brings in a team of tradesmen from Mitre 10 to help get all four apartments completed.

episodes.name: Episode 57
episodes.overview: Tonight, after ten weeks of renovating, the teams move out of The Block. Buyers arrive to inspect all the completed apartments and the judges score the completed apartments. There's $45,000 up for grabs.

episodes.name: The Auction
episodes.overview: It's the moment the contestants have all been waiting for. After weeks of hard work their beautiful completed apartments are open for inspection.

11.name: Season 11
11.overview: The Block takes determined couples, rundown apartments, and gives them equal-sized budgets and just weeks to out-renovate each other to see who becomes the ultimate winner.

episodes.name: The Biggest Block Begins
episodes.overview: Andy and Ben create an art deco inspired feature in their bedroom and Carlene is inspired by wallpaper for her room. Foreman Keith reminds all the contestants that heritage features must be restored.

episodes.name: Guest Bedrooms Continue
episodes.overview: Andy and Ben create an art deco inspired feature in their bedroom and Carlene is inspired by wallpaper for her room. Foreman Keith reminds all the contestants that heritage features must be restored.

episodes.name: Restoration and Re-purposing Challenge
episodes.overview: With four days until their guest bedrooms and walk in robes are due for judging, the teams are called to HQ for their first challenge, and the chance to win $5,000 cash and a bonus point! It's a restoration and re-purposing challenge.

episodes.name: Flooring Disaster
episodes.overview: Keith and Dan have bad news for Will and Karlie, who have planned on a concrete floor for a large portion of their apartment. Ben and Andy continue their practical jokes on baby boomers Dan and Carleen.

episodes.name: Guest Bedroom Reveals
episodes.overview: Its reveal time for five guest bedrooms, four walk in wardrobes and one ensuite bathroom that impresses all three judges. For one couple, feedback from the judges is devastating and things go from bad to worse when the scores are revealed.

episodes.name: Living and Dining Week Begins
episodes.overview: Another big week begins when the teams get started on their living and dining rooms. Planning the perfect space is key this week and a bitter feud begins for two couples.

episodes.name: $10,000 Challenge
episodes.overview: The teams have a chance to win a share of $10,000. They must create a home away from home at a Stayz property, embracing the artist and stylist within. Julia and Sasha struggle to see eye to eye on the planning of their dining room.

episodes.name: Mid Week Blues
episodes.overview: Its a gruelling week for all the teams. Ceilings must be redone, floors are ripped up and hefty fines are issued for after hours noise. Julia and Sasha's week goes from bad to worse.

episodes.name: Living and Dining Rooms Revealed
episodes.overview: It's the explosive end to a massive week of renovating. Julia and Sasha struggle to get their room finished and Julia isn't happy with the result. Ben and Andy, the self proclaimed style king, argue about their dining table.

episodes.name: Master Bedroom Week Begins
episodes.overview: The teams are battling it out for the most luxurious master bedrooms and walk in wardrobes they can afford. Dwindling budgets and tight deadlines keep everyone on their toes. The buyers jury judges the best apartment so far.

episodes.name: Bubbles Challenge
episodes.overview: The teams meet Scotty and Shelley for a soap making and wood turning challenge. There's a chance to win $5000 cash, and the winning soap will be stocked in David Jones stores across Australia.

episodes.name: Budget Blues
episodes.overview: As the week continues everyone is feeling the budget squeeze, and it goes from bad to worse for one team who are fined $2000 for using power tools after hours.

episodes.name: Master Bedrooms Revealed
episodes.overview: The teams race to reveal their master bedrooms and walk in robes. The judges are underwhelmed by some efforts then overwhelmed by impressive features and luxury finishes. Only one team can take home the much need $10,000 in prize money.

episodes.name: Hallway, Laundry and Powder Rooms
episodes.overview: The contestants begin their seventh week of renovating, with the hallways, laundries and powder rooms next on the agenda. Progress is very slow as teams hold each other up and Andy and Ben have major budget problems.

episodes.name: Tassie Road Trip Challenge
episodes.overview: The teams arrive in Devonport after a night on the Spirit of Tasmania. They meet Scotty and Shelley for a challenge where they must design a table for their terraces. It's an opportunity to win some rare and expensive Tasmanian timber.

episodes.name: Mid Week Mayhem
episodes.overview: Scotty and Shelley arrive at The Block to check on progress and discover that deadlines are getting the better of some contestants. It is mayhem with three areas to deliver, and some teams wonder if they'll finish their rooms.

episodes.name: Hallways, Laundries and Powder Rooms Revealed
episodes.overview: Tempers fray and frustration takes hold as it becomes clear that some teams will not finish. However there's plenty of wows from the judges, and one team walks away with $10,000.

episodes.name: Kitchen Week Begins
episodes.overview: After inspecting each other's hallways, laundries and powder rooms, friendships fracture. Attention quickly turns to kitchens and Keith and Dan call a meeting to ensure that all the kitchens are completed this week.

episodes.name: Challenge Day
episodes.overview: There's a chance for one team to win $5000 cash. With the help of a craftsman, each team must build a dining table for their terrace, in a theme allocated to them. Block All Stars Dan and Dani are guest judges.

episodes.name: Kitchen Week Chaos
episodes.overview: Kitchen week gets the better of the contestants and budgets are drying up. Designs take shape as installation begins but some teams aren't happy with the outcome.

episodes.name: Kitchens Revealed
episodes.overview: Its the end of kitchen week and the teams have put their very best efforts into delivering five unique and impressive kitchens. The judges have trouble deciding who will take home the $10,000.

episodes.name: Terrace and Re-do Rooms
episodes.overview: The most important week of renovating begins as the teams begin work on their terraces. Each team is given $5,000 to spend on their re-do room, and it's a chance to improve on the worst room they've delivered.

episodes.name: Budget Blues
episodes.overview: Work on the terraces and roof top garden continues and Keith and Dan go through each apartment with a long list of defects that need fixing. The teams have a chance to win some cash with a dinner party challenge.

episodes.name: Brendan Fevola Cooking Challenge
episodes.overview: The team who puts on the best dinner party for Brendan Fevola and partner Alex will win $6000 cash in tonight's challenge. Second place takes home $4000 so the stakes are high

episodes.name: Terraces Revealed
episodes.overview: Tonight the contestants hand over their completed terraces and re-do rooms. The judges are impressed but opinions are divided and the scores are tight. The teams discover Scotty's big secret as he reveals their final challenge.

episodes.name: The Final Challenge Begins
episodes.overview: Work on the challenge apartment begins and when the treasurer and project manager is appointed, alliances are formed and things get off to a rocky start.

episodes.name: Renovating Roller Coaster
episodes.overview: The challenge apartment takes shape and it's a roller coaster ride for the teams with sickness, stress and trouble. There's also a sleepover planned, Keith and Dan hand out the lists of defects.

episodes.name: Challenge Episode Takes Shape
episodes.overview: Scotty and Shelley arrive to check on progress. The teams have the chance to win $20,000, $15,000 or $10,000 off their reserves this week and the competition heats up.

episodes.name: Challenge Apartment Rooms Revealed
episodes.overview: Five rooms in the challenge apartment are completed. The judges decide which team has the advantage on auction day. First place receives $20,000 off their reserve price, second place $15,000 and third place $10,000 off their reserves.

episodes.name: Final Week Begins
episodes.overview: The contestants begin their final rooms in the challenge apartment. The budget blues hit hard as Kim's allocation of funds doesn't please any of the other teams and friendships are tested as ten weeks of renovating takes it's toll.

episodes.name: Budget Blues and Budget Wins
episodes.overview: Scotty arrives to talk budget with treasurer Kim and it isn't good news when Scotty is out of pocket. Kim has some welcome news for all the teams except for one. There's a chance to win $5000 cash in Scotty's last challenge.

episodes.name: Birthday Bash
episodes.overview: Scotty and Shelley inspect progress of the challenge apartment. All the Blockheads forget their differences and head out to celebrate Chris's birthday and the celebrations are full of surprises.

episodes.name: Final Challenge Rooms Revealed
episodes.overview: Tonight The Block is officially complete as the teams hand over their final rooms of the challenge apartment. There's a special guest judge and another chance to win $20,000, $15,000 or $10,000 off their reserve prices on auction day.

episodes.name: Party Time
episodes.overview: It's time for the contestants to celebrate all they have accomplished in 11 long weeks. Then the five weary teams move out and head home and the Block is open for inspection to the public for the first time.

episodes.name: Auction Day
episodes.overview: It's auction day and the five incredible Block apartments go under the hammer. There's plenty of tension and nerves as Scotty and the contestants watch their auctions unfold.

12.name: Season 12
12.overview: The Block takes determined couples, rundown apartments, and gives them equal-sized budgets and just weeks to out-renovate each other to see who becomes the ultimate winner.

episodes.name: 48 Hour Challenge
episodes.overview: Five new couples arrive at The Block to find five heritage houses Scott Cam has found and transported from around Victoria. They have just 48 hours to deliver a winning bedroom to get first pick of the houses.

episodes.name: Bathroom Week
episodes.overview: Our five teams start on day two of their main bathrooms. They are all busy finding trades, changing floor plans, selecting tiles and fixing problems, working double time to stay on track for room delivery in just four days.

episodes.name: Bathroom Week Struggles
episodes.overview: The Blockheads all face different challenges as they approach delivery day of their bathrooms. Site foreman, Keith, shuts down one house with the team having to stay the night with their neighbours.

episodes.name: Main Bathrooms Revealed
episodes.overview: It’s a frantic race to the finish as our couples deliver their incredible main bathrooms to the judges. Sadly one team doesn’t finish in time for tools down.

episodes.name: 1st Guest Bedroom Begins
episodes.overview: The couples start demolition and planning for their guest bedroom. Clint and Hannah have some big decisions to make around their unfinished bathroom. One contestant gets some sad news.

episodes.name: Guest Bedroom Judging
episodes.overview: It’s a tough decision for Block Judges Neale Whittaker, Shaynna Blaze and Darren Palmer, delivering the closest room judging scores in Block history.

episodes.name: Kids Bedroom Begins
episodes.overview: The team starts work on the kids bedrooms. One of the couples house is shut down and a block surprise brings an emotional reunion.

episodes.name: Kids Bedroom Continues and Challenge
episodes.overview: Everyone continues to plan and work on their kids room. One team calls the first body corporate meeting and it’s off to the Yarra Valley for a challenge to win some much needed prize money.

episodes.name: Kids Bedroom And Walk Arounds
episodes.overview: Scott and Shelley visit the teams and check on the progress of their kids bedrooms. There’s budget worries for one couple and foreman Keith catches one contestant trying to cheat.

episodes.name: Kids Bedroom Judging
episodes.overview: It’s a mad rush to the finish before tools down. Block judges Neale Whittaker, Shaynna Blaze and Darren Palmer are impressed with some rooms but others fall short. One team gets the first perfect score of 10 out of 10.

episodes.name: Anything But A Bedroom Begins
episodes.overview: The teams decide how to best use the room space and what type of room they will deliver to the judges this week, it can be anything but a Bedroom. Scott visits one couple for a budget intervention.

episodes.name: Anything But A Bedroom Continues
episodes.overview: One team is feeling the presssure which threatens to hold up the construction of the house extensions. It’s bad news for one couple as their plans for a pool in their backyard is squashed

episodes.name: Anything But a Bedroom and Challenge
episodes.overview: The teams head off for a challenge. They need to transform five rooms within Ronald McDonald House into sanctuaries for families visiting their sick children in the nearby hospital. One couple doesn’t finish in time for tools down.

episodes.name: Anything But A Bedroom Judging
episodes.overview: It’s a push to the finish line before tools down. The teams deliver a combination of home offices and lounge rooms to block  judges.

episodes.name: Living And Dining Commences
episodes.overview: It will be a challenge this week to get the right flow, from the older style front part of the houses to the new contemporary back extensions.

episodes.name: Living And Dining Continues
episodes.overview: The teams continue work on their living And dining rooms. A body corporate meeting results in one couple being accused of cheating.

episodes.name: Living And Dining And Challenge
episodes.overview: All the teams are busy working on their living And Dining rooms when they get a visit from Scott to announce its challenge day.

episodes.name: Living And Dining Judging
episodes.overview: It’s the final push to the finish line for the contestants to deliver their living and dining rooms. Block judges give two teams high scores but one team misses the mark.

episodes.name: Master Suite Commences
episodes.overview: The teams don’t have to renovate but build their master bedroom, en suite and walk-in robe: a massive 45 square meters

episodes.name: Master Suite and Challenge
episodes.overview: Everyone is feeling the pressure, resulting in some of the Blockheads bending the rules and another team about to give up. They all get arty on a challenge, competing to win a much needed $5000 in cash.

episodes.name: Master Suite Continues
episodes.overview: The pressure of finishing the biggest room ever in block history is starting to get to the couples. It’s a hive of activity in four of the houses but one team is three days behind.

episodes.name: Master Suite Judging
episodes.overview: Delivery of the biggest spaces ever on the programe is pushing everyone to their limits. Judges arrive to score the rooms.

episodes.name: Kitchen Commences
episodes.overview: The teams are busy preparing for their kitchen installs. Two contestants call a body corporate meeting; they need a unanimous vote to save them from being eliminated from the competition.

episodes.name: Kitchen And Challenge
episodes.overview: The kitchen installers arrive on site. Two contestants race to get their master suite and kitchen finished to avoid being eliminated from the competition.

episodes.name: Kitchen And Challenge Continues
episodes.overview: Two contestants are working around the clock to advoid being eliminated from the competition, while the other four teams join forces to renovate and style a five-star holiday accomodation.

episodes.name: Kitchen Judging
episodes.overview: It’s another mad rush for the teams to fi ish their kitchens for room reveal, but some contestants find time to help one team make the deadline to advoid being eliminated from the competition.

episodes.name: Hall And Laundry Commence
episodes.overview: The couples start planing their hallways and laundries. Three buyer advocates check out all the houses to give the teams feedback and the chance to win $10,000 towards their renovations.

episodes.name: Hall,Laundry And Challenge
episodes.overview: It’s all systems go for hall and Laundry week and the couples test drive their brand new kitchens with a challenge to produce their own signature dish.

episodes.name: Hall, Laundry And Challenge Continues
episodes.overview: The couples have been shopping and cooking in their new kitchens to produce their own signature dish. Celebrities Kate Langbroek and Dave Hughes join Scott and Shelley to judge the winner.

episodes.name: Hall And Laundry Judging
episodes.overview: The couples struggle to reach the finish line to deliver the hallways and laundries.

episodes.name: Guest Bedroom Commences

episodes.name: Backyards And Walk Arounds

episodes.name: Backyards Judging
episodes.overview: It’s been an exhausting week to finish their massive backyards, but the teams deliver five stunning outdoor spaces to the judges.

episodes.name: Studio And Garage Week Commences

episodes.name: Studios And Garages Continues
episodes.overview: The teams continue with the massive task to present their studios and garages in just one week. Foremans Keith and Dan continue with their defects check list

episodes.name: Studios And Garages Continue And Final Walk Arounds
episodes.overview: With a massive 100 meters to renovate everyone is under the pump getting their rooms ready for a night of painting. Scott and Shelley visit the teams and check out their rooms.

episodes.name: Studio And Garage Judging
episodes.overview: What the teams have achieved in one week is remarkable as they deliever five incredible studio apartments with walk in robes and en-suites.

episodes.name: Front Garden Commences
episodes.overview: It’s the final week of renovations and a big job for the teams to complete landscaping of the front yards, bring their facades to life with cladding and verandas.

episodes.name: Front Garden Continues And Teams Work On Their Defects Lists
episodes.overview: The teams continue work on their front gardens and have a huge amount of painting to get through, they have also been given a defects list by foreman Keith and Dan.

episodes.name: Front Gardens Continue
episodes.overview: With just a few days left on the block to complete their front gardens and defects list the teams are giving it all they’ve got get get to the finish line.

episodes.name: Front Garden Judging
episodes.overview: There’s still a lot of painting to be done as the teams approach the deadline for delivery of their front gardens and facades. They meet Scott at HQ for the judges comments and scores for the last time.

episodes.name: The Best Of The Block - Pimp My Pad Block Style

episodes.name: The Teams At Home And Public Open For Inspection

episodes.name: The Block Auctions
episodes.overview: After 12 weeks the houses go under the hammer. Couples compete for the first choice auction order and will win anything bid over their reserve with the highest over reserve taking an additional $100.000.

13.name: Season 13

episodes.name: Guest Bedroom Week (2)

episodes.name: Guest Bedroom Reveals

episodes.name: Master Ensuite
episodes.overview: It’s day one of a new room: master ensuite. One team feels the judges are being overly harsh towards them, and Keith catches another team cheating.

episodes.name: Kids Undercover Challenge

episodes.name: Master Ensuite

episodes.name: Master Ensuite Reveal
episodes.overview: It’s the day before the reveal, and three teams have issues with their shower screens. One couple are very upset with the judges feedback and want to leave the Block permanently.

episodes.name: Master Bedroom and Walk in Robe

episodes.name: Master Bedroom and Walk in Robe Reveal

episodes.name: Living & Dining Week Continues

episodes.name: Living & Dining Reveal

episodes.name: Kitchen Week

episodes.name: Steel Sculpture Challenge

episodes.name: Kitchen Week continues

episodes.name: Kitchen Reveal

episodes.name: Hallway, Laundry And Powder Room Week (1)

episodes.name: Hallway, Laundry and Powder Room Week (2)

episodes.name: Hallway, Laundry and Powder Room Week (3)

episodes.name: Hallway, Laundry and Powder Room Reveal
episodes.overview: Our illustrious judges return for the hallway, laundry and powder room reveals. As the most epic week so far comes to an end, one team’s terrible execution earns them a low score of 18.

episodes.name: Guest Bed and Re-do Room Week
episodes.overview: The Blockheads must tackle two rooms in guest bed and re-do room week. Jess wants to move their suspended fireplace and Norm battles with the decision.

episodes.overview: Money, money, money! All the Blockheads are very strapped for cash. After crisis talks with all the teams, Scott throws everyone a lifeline with a $25,000 Suncorp challenge.

episodes.name: Re-do Room Reveal and Judging
episodes.overview: Shaynna judges the re-do room challenge rooms, awarding one lucky team $10,000 from Suncorp.

episodes.name: Guest Bed Room Reveal
episodes.overview: The Blockheads reveal their second guest bedrooms to the judges and Scott treats all the teams to a very special surprise.

episodes.name: Terrace Week
episodes.overview: After eight gruelling weeks, it’s time for our Blockheads to confront, head on, the final piece of the puzzle. It’s terrace week and a battle of biblical proportions is sparked.

episodes.name: Terrace Week Continues
episodes.overview: After chatting with a paint specialist, Jess wants Norm to repaint their whole apartment.

episodes.name: Volkswagen Challenge
episodes.overview: Blockheads chopper to Phillip Island to race Volkswagen’s on a world famous Grand Prix track. Dan deals with multiple disasters back at the block.

episodes.name: Terrace Reveal
episodes.overview: Terrace Week draws to a close and it’s the final reveal of our Blockheads’ apartments, Neale, Shaynna and Darren return to score some amazing terraces.

episodes.name: Challenge Apartment Week One
episodes.overview: Our five teams begin Week one of the Challenge apartment. The rooms are allocated, and no one wants the dreaded hallway, but someone has to do it.

episodes.name: Challenge Apartment Week One
episodes.overview: After nominating Hayden as challenge apartment treasurer, Sara un-nominates him, giving all the power to the penthouses.

episodes.name: Challenge Apartment Week One (3)
episodes.overview: The scaffold around the exterior comes down and the glorious Gatwick is revealed.

episodes.name: Challenge Apartment Week One Reveals

episodes.name: Final Challenge Apartment Week
episodes.overview: The second and final week of the challenge apartment begins. The Blockheads compete for their last chance to knock some money off their reserve prices at auction.

episodes.name: Final Challenge Apartment Week (2)
episodes.overview: An argument erupts between Hans and Sara regarding Hayden’s unwillingness to help the group.

episodes.name: Final Challenge Apartment Week (3)
episodes.overview: There is two days until the last tool is downed on the Gatwick. Scott and Shelley visit the teams for one last walk around the Challenge apartment.

episodes.name: Final Challenge Apartment Room Reveals
episodes.overview: It’s the final room reveals of the series and what an amazing finish. The judges decide on the final amounts to be taken off each team’s reserve at auction.

episodes.name: Open For Inspections
episodes.overview: The Block is open for inspection. Thousands of people get the chance to check out the apartments before the auctions and meet their favourite Blockheads.

episodes.name: Auction
episodes.overview: After 12 weeks of renovation, five apartments go under the hammer. The teams win anything bid over their reserve and the team with the highest over reserve takes home an additional $100,000.

episodes.overview: Formal living room week sees Tess and Luke question whether they are cut out for this competition. The judges are stunned by the rooms our couples have revealed.

episodes.name: Master Bedrooms & Walk-in-Wardrobes Continue
episodes.overview: Fire hazards produce fireworks as Keith lays down the law, causing Matt to explode. Mitch and Mark’s grand plans cause Dan to hit the roof.

episodes.overview: Have Keith and Dan finally had enough of Jesse? Scott gives each couple one last chance to change their plans which have far-reaching ramifications come auction day.

episodes.overview: As couples start work on their second guest bedrooms, a serious safety breach occurs and someone is thrown off program for good.

episodes.overview: The Blockheads team up to create a million-dollar look room. Who will win the challenge? Could one of our favourite contestants actually be a thief?

episodes.name: Master Ensuites Reveal
episodes.overview: Our judges are blown away by the most stunning master ensuites ever. Who will take out the $10,000 cash?

episodes.overview: No one has enough money to finish, so the couples pull out all the stops to win the ever-important kitchen week. As we all know, kitchens sell homes.

episodes.overview: This episode, one team is going home with the golden gnome and $5000 in this special charity challenge.

episodes.name: Kitchens Reveal
episodes.overview: It’s judgement day for our couple’s kitchens. Who will wow the judges and take home the $10,000 prize money and the romantic trip away?

episodes.name: Living & Dinings Continue
episodes.overview: Is Jesse’s dark secret finally out? The previous season’s Blockhead Norm pays a visit with a surprise for our couples, and Norm’s partner Jess issues a challenge to our Blockheads.

episodes.name: Ronald McDonald  Challenge
episodes.overview: Who do Mitch and Mark accuse of cheating, live on radio? The fallout of these allegations rock the whole block.

episodes.name: Living & Dinings Reveal
episodes.overview: It's judging time for our couples' living and dining rooms. The judges are blown away by one room. It's a close call as to who will take the win and the $10,000 cash prize.

episodes.overview: One-hundred-and-fifty prospective buyers take a tour of the houses. Everyone is keen to hear feedback from people other than the judges. Who is on the right track, and who will be the buyer's choice?
